name: Frenzel_Geoprofile.txt
content:
# Required Packages
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(terra)
library(sf)
library(raster)
library(DT)
library(shinythemes)

# --- 1. CORE MATH ENGINE ---
rossmo_formula <- function(dist_km, B, f, g) {
  # Clamp ensures we never divide by exactly zero
  d <- terra::clamp(dist_km, lower = 0.0001)
  above <- d >= B
  below <- d < B
  
  part_above <- 1 / (d^f)
  part_below <- (B^(g - f)) / (abs(2 * B - d)^g)
  
  res <- (above * part_above) + (below * part_below)
  
  # Clean up mathematical artifacts
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(Inf, 0))
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(NaN, 0))
  return(res)
}

# --- 2. USER INTERFACE ---
ui <- fluidPage(
  theme = shinytheme("flatly"),
  titlePanel("Psych 403 Geographic Profiling Assignment"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      fileInput("file_upload", "1. Upload Crime Data (.txt/.csv)", accept = ".txt"),
      helpText("Ensure headers are 'latitude' and 'longitude'"),
      hr(),
      h4("Model Parameters"),
      sliderInput("buffer_b", "Rossmo Buffer (B) km:", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      sliderInput("decay_h", "Decay Constant (h):", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      hr(),
      h4("Display Settings"),
      sliderInput("res_val", "Resolution (Grid Size):", 40, 120, 60, 10),
      sliderInput("alpha_val", "Heatmap Opacity:", 0.1, 1.0, 0.6, 0.1),
      hr(),
      actionButton("run_calc", "Generate Profiles", class = "btn-primary btn-lg", width = "100%"),
      br(), br(),
      downloadButton("download_map", "Download Comparison (PNG)", class = "btn-success", style="width:100%")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      tabsetPanel(
        tabPanel("Rossmo Model", 
                 leafletOutput("map_rossmo", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Distance Decay", 
                 leafletOutput("map_decay", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Data Table", 
                 DT::dataTableOutput("comparison_table"))
      )
    )
  )
)

# --- 3. SERVER LOGIC ---
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  # Reactive: Data Loading
  points_data <- eventReactive(input$run_calc, {
    req(input$file_upload)
    df <- read.csv(input$file_upload$datapath, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    
    # Clean names
    names(df) <- tolower(trimws(names(df)))
    
    # Process numeric values for the uploaded Edmonton points 
    df$lat <- as.numeric(df$latitude)
    df$lon <- as.numeric(df$longitude)
    df <- df[is.finite(df$lat) & is.finite(df$lon), ]
    
    if(nrow(df) == 0) return(NULL)
    st_as_sf(df, coords = c("lon", "lat"), crs = 4326)
  })

  # Reactive: Spatial Calculations (Both Models)
  calc_results <- reactive({
    pts <- points_data()
    req(pts)
    
    bbox <- st_bbox(pts)
    grid_ext <- terra::ext(bbox[1]-0.05, bbox[3]+0.05, bbox[2]-0.05, bbox[4]+0.05)
    
    # Initialize grids with 0
    base_rast <- terra::rast(grid_ext, nrows = input$res_val, ncols = input$res_val, crs = "EPSG:4326")
    rossmo_sum <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    decay_sum  <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    
    v_pts <- terra::vect(pts)
    
    for(i in 1:nrow(v_pts)) {
      d_km <- terra::distance(base_rast, v_pts[i]) / 1000
      
      # Model 1: Rossmo
      rossmo_sum <- rossmo_sum + rossmo_formula(d_km, input$buffer_b, 1.2, 1.2)
      
      # Model 2: Simple Exponential Decay
      decay_sum <- decay_sum + exp(-input$decay_h * d_km)
    }
    
    # Normalization Helper
    norm_fn <- function(r) {
      m <- terra::global(r, "max", na.rm = TRUE)[1,1]
      if (!is.na(m) && m > 0) r/m else r
    }
    
    list(rossmo = norm_fn(rossmo_sum), decay = norm_fn(decay_sum))
  })

  # Map: Rossmo Output
  output$map_rossmo <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    r_layer <- raster::raster(res$rossmo)
    pal <- colorNumeric(c("transparent", "yellow", "orange", "red"), domain = c(0, 1), na.color = "transparent")
    
    leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>%
      addRasterImage(r_layer, colors = pal, opacity = input$alpha_val) %>%
      addCircleMarkers(data = points_data(), color = "black", radius = 4, weight = 2)
  })

  # Map: Decay Output
  output$map_decay <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    r_layer <- raster::raster(res$decay)
    pal <- colorNumeric(c("transparent", "cyan", "blue", "purple"), domain = c(0, 1), na.color = "transparent")
    
    leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>%
      addRasterImage(r_layer, colors = pal, opacity = input$alpha_val) %>%
      addCircleMarkers(data = points_data(), color = "black", radius = 4, weight = 2)
  })

  # Data Table View
  output$comparison_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    req(points_data())
    as.data.frame(st_coordinates(points_data()))
  })

  # Side-by-Side PNG Export
  output$download_map <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() { paste("model-comparison-", Sys.Date(), ".png", sep="") },
    content = function(file) {
      png(file, width = 1200, height = 600)
      par(mfrow=c(1,2))
      terra::plot(calc_results()$rossmo, main="Rossmo Model (Buffer Zone)")
      terra::plot(calc_results()$decay, main="Exponential Decay (Distance)")
      dev.off()
    }
  )
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

name: IT Hand Over.txt
content:
Project Handover: Geographic Profiling Lab
Description: A Shiny-based R application for spatial criminology. It compares Rossmoâ€™s Criminal Geographic Targeting (CGT) with Exponential Distance Decay models.

System Requirements for IT:

Language: R (version 4.1 or higher recommended).

Linux Dependencies: The server must have the following system libraries installed to support spatial math:

libgdal-dev (Geospatial Data Abstraction Library)

libgeos-dev (Geometry Engine)

libproj-dev (Cartographic Projections Library)

R Packages: shiny, leaflet, terra, sf, raster, DT, shinythemes.

Operational Notes:

The app uses the terra package for high-speed C++ based spatial calculations.

Memory management is optimized through vectorized operations and gc() triggers.

name: R Code Roy Profile Jan 1.txt
content:
# Required Packages
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(terra)
library(sf)
library(raster)
library(DT)
library(shinythemes)

# --- 1. CORE MATH ENGINE ---
rossmo_formula <- function(dist_km, B, f, g) {
  d <- terra::clamp(dist_km, lower = 0.0001)
  above <- d >= B
  below <- d < B
  part_above <- 1 / (d^f)
  part_below <- (B^(g - f)) / (abs(2 * B - d)^g)
  res <- (above * part_above) + (below * part_below)
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(Inf, 0))
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(NaN, 0))
  return(res)
}

# --- 2. USER INTERFACE ---
ui <- fluidPage(
  theme = shinytheme("flatly"),
  titlePanel("Psych 403 Geographic Profiling Assignment"),
  tags$p("Developed by R.R. Frenzel, PhD, RPsych", 
         style = "font-size: 14px; color: #555; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 20px;"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      fileInput("file_upload", "1. Upload Crime Data (.csv/.txt)", accept = c(".csv", ".txt")),
      actionButton("load_demo", "Load West Edmonton Demo", class = "btn-info", style="width:100%"),
      helpText("Ensure headers are 'latitude' and 'longitude'"),
      hr(),
      h4("Model Parameters"),
      sliderInput("buffer_b", "Rossmo Buffer (B) km:", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      sliderInput("decay_h", "Decay Constant (h):", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      hr(),
      h4("Display Settings"),
      sliderInput("res_val", "Resolution (Grid Size):", 40, 120, 60, 10),
      sliderInput("alpha_val", "Heatmap Opacity:", 0.1, 1.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      hr(),
      actionButton("run_calc", "Generate Profiles", class = "btn-primary btn-lg", width = "100%"),
      br(), br(),
      downloadButton("download_map", "Download Comparison (PNG)", class = "btn-success", style="width:100%")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      tabsetPanel(
        tabPanel("Rossmo Model", leafletOutput("map_rossmo", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Distance Decay", leafletOutput("map_decay", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Data Table", DT::dataTableOutput("comparison_table"))
      )
    )
  )
)

# --- 3. SERVER LOGIC ---
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  rigel_palette <- c("transparent", "#4B0082", "#0000FF", "#00FFFF", "#00FF00", "#FFFF00", "#FF7F00", "#FF0000")

  # Use a reactiveVal to store points so we can switch between upload and demo
  points_store <- reactiveVal(NULL)

  # Handle Uploaded Data
  observeEvent(input$file_upload, {
    # Added robust CSV reading to handle quotes properly
    df <- read.csv(input$file_upload$datapath, stringsAsFactors = FALSE, quote = "\"'\"", strip.white = TRUE)
    names(df) <- tolower(trimws(names(df)))
    df$lat <- as.numeric(df$latitude)
    df$lon <- as.numeric(df$longitude)
    df <- df[is.finite(df$lat) & is.finite(df$lon), ]
    if(nrow(df) > 0) points_store(st_as_sf(df, coords = c("lon", "lat"), crs = 4326))
  })

  # Handle Demo Data
  observeEvent(input$load_demo, {
    demo_df <- data.frame(
      latitude = c(53.5225, 53.5251, 53.5310, 53.5180, 53.5295, 53.5402, 53.5120, 53.5450, 53.5260, 53.5080, 53.5350, 53.5155, 53.5480, 53.5205, 53.5275),
      longitude = c(-113.6242, -113.6105, -113.6350, -113.6420, -113.5980, -113.6050, -113.6150, -113.6280, -113.6550, -113.6310, -113.5850, -113.5920, -113.6100, -113.6650, -113.6210)
    )
    points_store(st_as_sf(demo_df, coords = c("longitude", "latitude"), crs = 4326))
  })

  calc_results <- eventReactive(input$run_calc, {
    pts <- points_store()
    req(pts)
    bbox <- st_bbox(pts)
    grid_ext <- terra::ext(bbox[1]-0.05, bbox[3]+0.05, bbox[2]-0.05, bbox[4]+0.05)
    base_rast <- terra::rast(grid_ext, nrows = input$res_val, ncols = input$res_val, crs = "EPSG:4326")
    rossmo_sum <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    decay_sum  <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    v_pts <- terra::vect(pts)
    for(i in 1:nrow(v_pts)) {
      d_km <- terra::distance(base_rast, v_pts[i]) / 1000
      rossmo_sum <- rossmo_sum + rossmo_formula(d_km, input$buffer_b, 1.2, 1.2)
      decay_sum <- decay_sum + exp(-input$decay_h * d_km)
    }
    norm_fn <- function(r) {
      m <- terra::global(r, "max", na.rm = TRUE)[1,1]
      if (!is.na(m) && m > 0) r/m else r
    }
    list(rossmo = norm_fn(rossmo_sum), decay = norm_fn(decay_sum))
  })

  render_geo_map <- function(rast_data, pts, alpha) {
    r_layer <- raster::raster(rast_data)
    pal <- colorNumeric(palette = rigel_palette, domain = c(0, 1), na.color = "transparent")
    leaflet() %>% addTiles() %>%
      addRasterImage(r_layer, colors = pal, opacity = alpha) %>%
      addCircleMarkers(data = pts, color = "white", fillColor = "black", radius = 5, weight = 2, fillOpacity = 1) %>%
      addLegend(pal = pal, values = c(0, 1), title = "Priority Index",
                labFormat = labelFormat(prefix = "(Low) ", suffix = " (High)"), position = "bottomright")
  }

  output$map_rossmo <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    render_geo_map(res$rossmo, points_store(), input$alpha_val)
  })

  output$map_decay <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    render_geo_map(res$decay, points_store(), input$alpha_val)
  })

  output$comparison_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    req(points_store())
    as.data.frame(st_coordinates(points_store()))
  })

  output$download_map <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() { paste("model-comparison-", Sys.Date(), ".png", sep="") },
    content = function(file) {
      png(file, width = 1200, height = 600)
      par(mfrow=c(1,2))
      terra::plot(calc_results()$rossmo, main="Rossmo Model (Priority)")
      terra::plot(calc_results()$decay, main="Distance Decay (Priority)")
      dev.off()
    }
  )
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

      addCircleMarkers(data = pts, color = "white", fillColor = "black", 
                       radius = 5, weight = 2, fillOpacity = 1) %>%
      addLegend(pal = pal, values = c(0, 1),
                title = "Search Priority",
                labFormat = labelFormat(suffix = "%", transform = function(x) 100 * x),
                position = "bottomright")
  }
  
  output$map_rossmo <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    render_geo_map(res$rossmo, points_data(), input$alpha_val)
  })
  
  output$map_decay <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results()
    req(res)
    render_geo_map(res$decay, points_data(), input$alpha_val)
  })
  
  # Data Table View [cite: 10]
  output$comparison_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    req(points_data())
    as.data.frame(st_coordinates(points_data()))
  })
  
  # PNG Export
  output$download_map <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() { paste("model-comparison-", Sys.Date(), ".png", sep="") },
    content = function(file) {
      png(file, width = 1200, height = 600)
      par(mfrow=c(1,2))
      terra::plot(calc_results()$rossmo, main="Rossmo Model")
      terra::plot(calc_results()$decay, main="Distance Decay")
      dev.off()
    }
  )
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

name: Student Data Requirements.txt
content:
Student Data Requirements
To ensure the app processes the coordinates correctly, the uploaded .txt or .csv file must meet these criteria:

Headers: The file must have columns named exactly latitude and longitude.

Format: Use decimal degrees (e.g., 49.2827, -123.1207) rather than degrees/minutes/seconds.

Cleaning: Ensure there are no empty rows or text characters in the coordinate columns.

Pro-Tip for Canvas
If you notice the app looks a bit "cramped" on mobile devices or smaller laptops, you can adjust the height="800px" in that iFrame code I gave you to a larger number, like 1000px, to give the maps more breathing room.

Would you like me to generate a sample "Template.csv" file that you can provide to your students as a starting point?

name: app.r
content:
# Required Packages
library(shiny)
library(leaflet)
library(terra)
library(DT)
library(shinythemes)

# Force-load hidden dependencies for Shinylive/Wasm
library(munsell)
library(colorspace)
library(scales)

# --- 1. CORE MATH ENGINE ---
rossmo_formula <- function(dist_km, B, f, g) {
  d <- terra::clamp(dist_km, lower = 0.0001)
  above <- d >= B
  below <- d < B
  
  part_above <- 1 / (d^f)
  part_below <- (B^(g - f)) / (abs(2 * B - d)^g)
  
  res <- (above * part_above) + (below * part_below)
  
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(Inf, 0))
  res <- terra::classify(res, cbind(NaN, 0))
  return(res)
}

# --- 2. USER INTERFACE ---
ui <- fluidPage(
  theme = shinytheme("flatly"),
  titlePanel("Psych 403 Geographic Profiling Assignment"),
  tags$p("R.R. Frenzel, PhD, RPsych", 
         style = "font-size: 14px; color: #555; margin-top: -10px; margin-bottom: 20px;"),
  
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      fileInput("file_upload", "1. Upload Crime Data (.csv)", accept = c(".csv", ".txt")),
      helpText("Ensure headers are 'latitude' and 'longitude'"),
      hr(),
      h4("Model Parameters"),
      sliderInput("buffer_b", "Rossmo Buffer (B) km:", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      sliderInput("decay_h", "Decay Constant (h):", 0.1, 3.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      hr(),
      h4("Display Settings"),
      sliderInput("res_val", "Resolution (Grid Size):", 40, 120, 60, 10),
      sliderInput("alpha_val", "Heatmap Opacity:", 0.1, 1.0, 0.5, 0.1),
      hr(),
      actionButton("run_calc", "Generate Profiles", class = "btn-primary btn-lg", width = "100%"),
      br(), br(),
      # --- TWO DOWNLOAD BUTTONS ---
      downloadButton("download_map", "Download Map (PNG)", class = "btn-success", style="width:100%"),
      br(), br(),
      downloadButton("download_csv", "Download Data (CSV)", class = "btn-info", style="width:100%")
    ),
    
    mainPanel(
      tabsetPanel(
        tabPanel("Rossmo Model", 
                 leafletOutput("map_rossmo", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Distance Decay", 
                 leafletOutput("map_decay", height = "650px")),
        tabPanel("Data Table", 
                 DT::dataTableOutput("comparison_table"))
      )
    )
  )
)

# --- 3. SERVER LOGIC ---
server <- function(input, output, session) {
  
  rigel_palette <- c("transparent", "#4B0082", "#0000FF", "#00FFFF", "#00FF00", "#FFFF00", "#FF7F00", "#FF0000")
  
  points_df <- eventReactive(input$run_calc, {
    req(input$file_upload)
    df <- read.csv(input$file_upload$datapath, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
    names(df) <- tolower(trimws(names(df)))
    df$lat <- as.numeric(df$latitude)
    df$lon <- as.numeric(df$longitude)
    df <- df[is.finite(df$lat) & is.finite(df$lon), ]
    return(df)
  })
  
  calc_results <- reactive({
    df <- points_df()
    req(nrow(df) > 0)
    
    v_pts <- terra::vect(df, geom = c("lon", "lat"), crs = "EPSG:4326")
    e <- terra::ext(v_pts)
    grid_ext <- terra::ext(e[1]-0.05, e[2]+0.05, e[3]-0.05, e[4]+0.05)
    
    base_rast <- terra::rast(grid_ext, nrows = input$res_val, ncols = input$res_val, crs = "EPSG:4326")
    rossmo_sum <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    decay_sum  <- terra::init(base_rast, 0)
    
    for(i in 1:nrow(v_pts)) {
      d_km <- terra::distance(base_rast, v_pts[i]) / 1000
      rossmo_sum <- rossmo_sum + rossmo_formula(d_km, input$buffer_b, 1.2, 1.2)
      decay_sum <- decay_sum + exp(-input$decay_h * d_km)
    }
    
    norm_fn <- function(r) {
      m <- terra::global(r, "max", na.rm = TRUE)[1,1]
      if (!is.na(m) && m > 0) r/m else r
    }
    
    list(rossmo = norm_fn(rossmo_sum), decay = norm_fn(decay_sum), points = v_pts)
  })
  
  render_geo_map <- function(rast_data, v_pts, alpha) {
    pal <- colorNumeric(palette = rigel_palette, domain = c(0, 1), na.color = "transparent")
    leaflet() %>% 
      addTiles() %>%
      addRasterImage(raster::raster(rast_data), colors = pal, opacity = alpha) %>%
      addCircleMarkers(lng = terra::crds(v_pts)[,1], lat = terra::crds(v_pts)[,2], 
                       color = "white", fillColor = "black", radius = 5, weight = 2, fillOpacity = 1) %>%
      addLegend(pal = pal, values = c(0, 1), title = "Search Priority",
                labFormat = labelFormat(suffix = "%", transform = function(x) 100 * x), position = "bottomright")
  }
  
  output$map_rossmo <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results(); render_geo_map(res$rossmo, res$points, input$alpha_val)
  })
  
  output$map_decay <- renderLeaflet({
    res <- calc_results(); render_geo_map(res$decay, res$points, input$alpha_val)
  })
  
  output$comparison_table <- DT::renderDataTable({
    points_df()
  })
  
  # --- DOWNLOAD HANDLER: MAP (PNG) ---
  output$download_map <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() { paste("profiling-map-", Sys.Date(), ".png", sep="") },
    content = function(file) {
      png(file, width = 1200, height = 600, res = 100)
      try({
        res <- calc_results()
        par(mfrow = c(1, 2), mar = c(4, 4, 3, 2))
        static_cols <- c("white", "#4B0082", "#0000FF", "#00FFFF", "#00FF00", "#FFFF00", "#FF7F00", "#FF0000")
        terra::plot(res$rossmo, main = "Rossmo Model", col = static_cols)
        terra::plot(res$points, add = TRUE, col = "black", pch = 16, cex = 1.5)
        terra::plot(res$decay, main = "Distance Decay", col = static_cols)
        terra::plot(res$points, add = TRUE, col = "black", pch = 16, cex = 1.5)
      }, silent = TRUE)
      dev.off()
    }
  )
  
  # --- DOWNLOAD HANDLER: DATA (CSV) ---
  output$download_csv <- downloadHandler(
    filename = function() { paste("profiling-data-", Sys.Date(), ".csv", sep="") },
    content = function(file) {
      write.csv(points_df(), file, row.names = FALSE)
    }
  )
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)

name: github instructions.txt
content:
That is fantastic news! Getting a Shinylive app through the export process is the hardest part. Since your app is now "serverless" (it runs entirely in the student's browser), you can host it anywhere that allows static files.

For Canvas, the best approach is to host the files on GitHub Pages (which is free and reliable) and then "embed" the app into your Canvas page using an iFrame.

Step 1: Upload to GitHub
Create a GitHub Account: If you donâ€™t have one, sign up at github.com.

Create a New Repository: Name it something like criminal-conduct-app. Make sure it is set to Public.

Upload the 'site' Folder:

Open your new repository on GitHub.

Click Add file > Upload files.

Drag and drop everything inside your D:/.../site folder (not the 'site' folder itself, just its contents) into the browser.

Wait for the hundreds of small files in the shinylive folder to upload, then click Commit changes.

Step 2: Turn on GitHub Pages
In your GitHub repository, go to Settings (top tab).

Click Pages on the left-hand sidebar.

Under "Build and deployment", set the source to Deploy from a branch.

Select main (or master) and the /(root) folder, then click Save.

Wait about 2â€“3 minutes. GitHub will provide a URL like: https://yourusername.github.io/criminal-conduct-app/.

Step 3: Embed in Canvas
Now that your app is live on the internet, you can put it inside your Canvas course:

Go to your Canvas Course and create a new Page.

In the Rich Content Editor (the text box), click the HTML View icon (looks like </>).

Paste the following code, replacing the URL with your GitHub Pages URL:

HTML

<iframe 
    src="https://yourusername.github.io/criminal-conduct-app/" 
    width="100%" 
    height="800px" 
    style="border:none;" 
    allow="geolocation; microphone; camera">
</iframe>
Click Save & Publish.

Why this is better for Canvas
No Login Required: Students don't need an R account.

Stability: The app won't "go to sleep" like it might on a free ShinyApps.io account.

Performance: Once the browser downloads the files, the calculations (the Rossmo formula) happen instantly on the student's computer.

Would you like me to help you draft the instructions for your students on how to format their .csv files so they don't get errors when uploading their data?
